.TH "vdso_update_begin" 9 "vdso_update_begin" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vdso_update_begin \- Start of a VDSO update section
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" vdso_update_begin
.BI "(void "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "void" 12
no arguments
.SH "DESCRIPTION"

Allows architecture code to safely update the architecture specific VDSO
data. Disables interrupts, acquires timekeeper lock to serialize against
concurrent updates from timekeeping and invalidates the VDSO data
sequence counter to prevent concurrent readers from accessing
inconsistent data.
.SH "RETURN"
Saved interrupt flags which need to be handed in to
\fBvdso_update_end\fP.
